> Truffle Ticket #479917 [Pending] `artifacts.require` dependency of dependency bug

> **Notice** I have found a workaround, however, I am still submitting this as an Issue due to framework behavior and error messag. For those only interested in solutions, skip to the "Attempts at Resolution" section and review steps `5` and `6` (second to last section of this OP)

---------------------------

## Issue

I'm running into an interesting bug when I introduce an `interface` to a project, that persists **even after** removal of the `interface`. To be clear, prior to introduction of an `interface` contract, Truffle has **no** issue finding and linking various dependencies.


Additionally this bug seems to be reproducible when linking a `library` that is a dependency of a development dependency. Because when adding an `interface` contract to a project that directly depends on an external `library` there are no issues.


______


## Steps to Reproduce


0. Clone `string-storage`

```bash
git clone https://github.com/solidity-utilities/string-storage.git
```


1. Check out `v0.0.1` tag

```bash
pushd string-storage

git checkout v0.0.1
```


2. Install NPM dependencies

```bash
npm ci
```


3. Run tests before adding `interface` file

```bash
npm test
```


4. Add `contracts/InterfaceStringStorage.sol` file, and re-run tests to generate persistent error

> Note, I've recently tested with an empty `interface` contract and similar errors are thrown.


```solidity
// SPDX-License-Identifier: AGPL-3.0
pragma solidity 0.8.7;

///
interface InterfaceStringStorage {
    ///
    function data(string memory) external view returns (string memory);
    ///
    function indexes(string memory) external view returns (uint256);
    ///
    function keys(uint256) external view returns (string memory);
    ///
    function owner() external view returns (address);
    ///
    function addAuthorized(address _key) external;
    ///
    function changeOwner(address _new_owner) external;
    ///
    function clear() external;
    ///
    function deleteAuthorized(address _key) external;
    ///
    function get(string memory _key) external view returns (string memory);
    ///
    function getOrElse(string memory _key, string memory _default) external view returns (string memory);
    ///
    function getOrError(string memory _key, string memory _reason) external view returns (string memory);
    ///
    function has(string memory _key) external view returns (bool);
    ///
    function indexOf(string memory _key) external view returns (uint256);
    ///
    function indexOfOrError(string memory _key, string memory _reason) external view returns (uint256);
    ///
    function listKeys() external view returns (string[] memory);
    ///
    function remove(string memory _key) external returns (string memory);
    ///
    function removeOrError(string memory _key, string memory _reason) external returns (string memory);
    ///
    function selfDestruct(address _to) external;
    ///
    function set(string memory _key, string memory _value) external;
    ///
    function setOrError(string memory _key, string memory _value, string memory _reason) external;
    ///
    function size() external view returns (uint256);
}
```


5. Remove `contracts/InterfaceStringStorage.sol` file, and re-run tests to continue generating persistent error


______


## Expected Behavior


I expect tests to continue to pass... well that is until I write something to explicitly break 'em.


______


