> Note, to be absolutely clear this error only appears when an `interface` contract is added to `contracts/` directory of the `string-storage` project.
>
> Furthermore, this bug is persistent in that errors remain even after removing the `interface` contract.
>
> The similar project `address-storage` is built much the same, eg. it too has an `interface` contract, but has **no** such errors reported.


______


## Environment

* Operating System: Linux
* Ethereum client: ganache-cli 6.12.2
* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.4.18
* node version (`node --version`): v16.11.0
* npm version (`npm --version`): 8.0.0


______


## Attempts at Resolution


0. Defined `LibraryMappingAddress` as a development dependency, eg.

```bash
pushd ~/git/hub/solidity-utilities/string-storage

npm install --save-dev @solidity-utilities/library-mapping-address
```


1. Defined various paths to `LibraryMappingAddress`, eg.

```javascript
  /* ... */
  const LibraryMappingAddress = artifacts.require("@solidity-utilities/library-mapping-address/contracts/LibraryMappingAddress");
  /* ... */
  const LibraryMappingAddress = artifacts.require("@solidity-utilities/library-mapping-address/LibraryMappingAddress");
  /* ... */
  const LibraryMappingAddress = artifacts.require("library-mapping-address/LibraryMappingAddress");
  /* ... */
  const LibraryMappingAddress = artifacts.require("library-mapping-address/contracts/LibraryMappingAddress");
  /* ... */
  const LibraryMappingAddress = artifacts.require("../node_modules/@solidity-utilities/library-mapping-address/contracts/LibraryMappingAddress");
```

> Note, I tried each with and without the `.sol` file extension too


2. Ran tests via globally installed `truffle`, eg.

```bash
pushd ~/git/hub/solidity-utilities/string-storage

truffle test
```


3. Ran tests via NPX


```bash
pushd ~/git/hub/solidity-utilities/string-storage

npx truffle test
```


4. Ran tests via direct node modules path


```bash
pushd ~/git/hub/solidity-utilities/string-storage

node node_modules/truffle/build/cli.bundled.js test
```


5. Removed `build/` directory and re-ran tests

```bash
pushd ~/git/hub/solidity-utilities/string-storage

rm -rf build/

npm test
```


6. Linked all `library` contracts with all other `contract` files


```javascript
"use strict";

module.exports = (deployer, network, accounts) => {
  if (network !== "development") {
    return;
  }

  console.log("Notice: detected network of development kind ->", { network });

  const LibraryMappingAddress = artifacts.require("LibraryMappingAddress");
  const AddressStorage = artifacts.require("AddressStorage");

  const LibraryMappingString = artifacts.require("LibraryMappingString");
  const StringStorage = artifacts.require("StringStorage");

  const Account = artifacts.require("Account");
  const Host = artifacts.require("Host");

  const StringStorage__owner = accounts[0];
  const AddressStorage__owner = accounts[1];
  const Account__owner = accounts[2];
  const Host__owner = accounts[3];
  const Host__fee = 100;

  // LibraryMappingString.address = "0x0...";
  deployer.deploy(LibraryMappingString, { overwrite: false });

  // LibraryMappingAddress.address = "0x1...";
  deployer.deploy(LibraryMappingAddress, { overwrite: false });

  deployer.link(LibraryMappingAddress, [
    AddressStorage,
    StringStorage,
    Account,
    Host,
  ]);

  deployer.link(LibraryMappingString, [
    AddressStorage,
    StringStorage,
    Account,
    Host,
  ]);

  deployer.deploy(AddressStorage, AddressStorage__owner);
  deployer.deploy(StringStorage, StringStorage__owner);

  deployer.deploy(Account, Account__owner);
  deployer.deploy(Host, Host__owner, Host__fee);
};
```

... Up 'till "Attempts at Resolution" step `4` no joy though, and perhaps most bothersome is this bug persists even after removal of `contracts/InterfaceStringStorage.sol` file.

However, turns out that "Attempts at Resolution" step `5` combined with step `6` lossened things up such that tests began to compile, run, and pass!


______


